Sotik, Kenya: Two APS constables guarding a KCPE Examination Container at Sotik Sub-County Commissioner&rsquo;s offices, shot at each other after an argument. They were both armed with G3 rifles. It is reported that after a brief exchange of words in anger, they resorted to an exchange of fire, critically injuring each other.&nbsp; They were rushed to Tenwek Mission Hospital where they are admitted in serious condition. &nbsp;The scene was visited by commanders from Bomet and Sotik and both rifles recovered. Police have launched probe into the incident.